    "narrative": "The offensive core for the Austin Waves today is headlined by **Gunnar Henderson**, who earns our highest efficiency score of 81.88. Facing a favorable matchup against Bello, **Gunnar Henderson** benefits from a massive 16% park adjustment and a 14% platoon advantage, cementing his role as our primary catalyst at the top of the order. **Kyle Tucker** also projects as an elite play (73.75) against Taillon; while we await official lineup confirmation, his projected #4 slot and high xwOBA make him a locked-in cornerstone for run production. Meanwhile, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (66.25) remains a staple against Williams, utilizing a strong SP skill adjustment to overcome a slight platoon disadvantage, ensuring he remains a high-floor producer in the middle of our lineup.\n\nDeep-roster efficiency is buoyed by **Nasim Nunez** (60.13), whose aggressive utilization of his switch-hitting ability and the favorable matchup against Hudson allows him to edge out our bench options. The decision to start **Nasim Nunez** over **Brady House** (52.73) was the most difficult call of the morning. While **Brady House** carries a high ceiling, the optimizer favored the specific situational efficiency of **Nasim Nunez** and the platoon-stable **Andy Pages** (60.68) against Taillon. **Marcell Ozuna** was considered, but his score cratered to 42.53 due to the elite 2.90 xERA of Woodruff, forcing him to the pine to protect our daily game caps. We are monitoring the status of **Liam Hicks**, **Heliot Ramos**, and **Andy Pages** closely; as their lineups are currently pending, any shift in their batting order could necessitate a late-day adjustment to maximize our potential for stolen bases and counting stats.",
